dialogue: May I confirm that is yours?
Here you go. Take it.
Huh.
Swim.
Allow me to introduce myself. Fink. Predator and local goose expert. Which I know you could use about now.
You are the destroyer unit.
It’s okay, I won’t eat him.
Are you crazy, I might eat him.
You said you would not.
Do you believe everything you hear?
Yes.
Noted.
Why did you steal my gosling?
I’m a fox. I do foxy things. It’s in my nature.
Your, programming.
Why’d you help me?
I’m a robot. I do robotty things. I seek tasks and ensure all essential needs have been met or exceeded.
I have some essential needs.
I thought you’d never ask. Let’s start with eat.
Yeah, yeah, yeah, right there.
I do not think these are suitable.
Wait, wait, lemme check.
Ooh. Mmm. Seems good to me.
Say...can You make yourself look like a bear?
I’m here for a honey lunch.
I believe I am under attack.
You’re doing great.
Should I be concerned?
Sorry, can’t hear you.
Here you go, kid.
How do goslings normally do this?
This is not working.
Are you kidding? Everything is working great.
Oh, yeah that. Here.
Phase one of task is completed.
Now, we’re gonna have to do all this over tomorrow. All these kids do is eat.
I understand.
What’s that?
My power core. It is damaged. Without it I rely on my solar surfaces and batteries.
Yeah, you should work on that.
I also need a replacement transmitter.
Ugh, do I have to do everything? When we run across another robot we’ll kill it and take its transmitter.
Negative. Rozzum inhibition protocols prevent deliberate harm to others.
Look. You need to learn how things work on this island.
Me, the bear, everybody, we’re all just trying to survive. And kindness, is not a survival skill.
Yeah. So, uh, how’d you get a gosling, anyways?
There was an accident. I terminated his family.
For future reference, you probably want to keep all that to yourself.
Understood. Do not mention dead family. Fink, how long do you estimate swim and fly to take?
Swimming’s easy. I can teach him the way my mom taught me. Swim.
Fink! He will not learn that way.
Not if you keep doing that.
Just between us, this whole thing may not take as long as you think. Your gosling, he isn’t exactly normal.
I have a defective baby?
He’s what they call a ‘runt’.
A runt.
Fact is, even if his whole family hadn’t been killed, he probably wouldn’t have lived very long. Just, I don’t know. Don’t get too attached to the little guy, that’s all.
If you want, I could eat him right now and save you the grief later.
Negative. Eating this task is not the same as completing it.
So we’re doing this. Well, if you don’t want me or anyone else to eat him, you’re going to need a place that’s safer than out here... which is a great idea! New project!
Is it normal to burp this much?
Paddler? Local laughing stock. Spends every day trying to cut down the biggest tree on the island. He’s obsessed. Kind of like you and your task hang up.
His, programming?
Hey Paddler. You’re never going to finish that.
Are you sure Paddler will not mind us borrowing his home?
He doesn’t need to know.
Seriously? He needs room for me and my stuff.
Better. Now, you can make one this big, right?
No task is impossible for Rozzum Seven One Three Four.
